Message.MsgText: ORDERED_TRANSACTED_RECEIVE_ERROR_CWSIP0180=CWSIP0180E: The destination with name {0} on messaging engine {1} is receive disallowed due to a current transacted receive taking place.

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_START_ERROR_SIMP0651=CWSIP0651E: The local mediation point for destination {0} has been told to start mediating messages, but cannot because a configuration change has occurred to remove that mediation from the destination.
Message.Explanation: A mediation is no longer defined on the destination, so the request to start the mediation point has resulted in an error.
Message.UserResponse: No user action is required. The mediation point will be removed shortly.

Message.MsgText: CREATE_BIFURCATED_CONSUMER_ERROR_CWSIP0094=CWSIP0094E: Unable to create BifurcatedConsumer to original consumer {0} on messaging engine {1} as they have different user ids.

Message.MsgText: DESTINATION_NOT_FOUND_ERROR_CWSIP0341=CWSIP0341W: The destination {0} was not found on messaging engine {1}.
Message.Explanation: The named destination is unknown on the local messaging engine.
Message.UserResponse: =Check that the destination name is correct. If the destination exists on another messaging engine, ensure that communication with the other messaging engine is working.

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_START_PREVENTED_DISABLED_SIMP0665=CWSIP0665E: The mediation point for destination {0} cannot start because the mediation is disabled for that destination.
Message.Explanation: The configuration information indicates that all mediation activity on this destination is disabled.
Message.UserResponse: When mediations are to work, the destination must indicate that mediations are enabled.

Message.MsgText: LINK_NOT_FOUND_ERROR_CWSIP0041=CWSIP0041E: The link with name {0} was not found on messaging engine {1}.

Message.UserResponse: Make the state between the two messaging engines consistent. Either by recovering the two message stores to the same point in time or cancelling this request on the receiving messaging engine.

Message.MsgText: MOVE_MESSAGES_FROM_EXCEPTION_DESTINATION_INFO_CWSIP0292=CWSIP0292I: {0} messages have been moved from the exception destination {1} to the destination {2} during the time specified {3} {4}.
Message.Explanation: The command result indicates the number of messages that have been moved from the exception destination that is mapped to the destination provided in the input. The selection criteria is used in conjunction with the selection criteria of the subscriber while moving the messages. The time specified is the time taken for the republish operation to run.
Message.UserResponse: If no messages are moved then check if the selection criteria provided in conjunction with the selection criteria on the subscriber maps to any message in the exception destination. If messages have been successfully moved then check if there are more messages to be moved. If there are more messages to be moved, then rerun republishEDMessages command to complete the process.

Message.UserResponse: Investigate whether the rate of production of messages for transfer over this link is too high.

Message.MsgText: OPERATION_IS_INVALID_ERROR_CWSIP0121=CWSIP0121E: The operation attempted is incorrect on the destination {0} on messaging engine {1}.
Message.Explanation: The destination does not support this operation.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_MESSAGE_PUMP_START_PRODUCER_FAILED_SIMP0666=CWSIP0666W: The mediation point for destination {0} on bus {1} failed to create a Producer due to error {2}

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_EXCEPTION_CWSIP0814=CWSIP0814W: An exception {0} occurred when attempting to send a message to the mediation point associated with destination {1} associated with the WebSphere MQ Server bus member {2}.

Message.MsgText: PUTEXCEPTION_DISCONNECT_CONSUMER_CWSIP0473=CWSIP0473E: An exception {2} occurred when putting a remote message, on destination {0} localised at messaging engine {1}, into the local Persistent Store.

Message.MsgText: USER_NOT_AUTH_BROWSE_ERROR_CWSIP0304=CWSIP0304E: Browse access to destination {0} was denied for subject {1}

Message.MsgText: SUBSCRIPTION_DOESNT_EXIST_ERROR_CWSIP0072=CWSIP0072E: Durable subscription with name {0} does not exist on messaging engine {1}.
Message.Explanation: An attempt has been made to access a durable subscription with the given name and this subscription does not exist.
Message.UserResponse: Either create the durable subscription with the given name, or try again with a valid durable subscription identifier.

Message.MsgText: MOVE_MESSAGES_FROM_EXCEPTION_DESTINATION_ERROR_CWSIP0294=CWSIP0294E: The exception destination is not configured for the destination provided.
Message.Explanation: The destination provided in the input does not have an exception destination configured.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the input destination is correct. Some of the possible causes could be that the input destination provided is either an exception destination or a system destination.

Message.MsgText: MOVE_MESSAGES_FROM_EXCEPTION_DESTINATION_ERROR_CWSIP0293=CWSIP0293E: An instance of the message republishing operation from an exception destination is already in progress in the current messaging engine. Try to move the messages after the active operation is completed.
Message.Explanation: An instance of the message republishing operation from an exception destination is already in progress in the current messaging engine. Try to move the messages after the active operation is completed.
Message.UserResponse: Check if there is another instance of the same operation being executed. Wait for the active instance to complete before you rerun the command.

Message.MsgText: SUBSCRIPTION_ATTACH_FAILED_CWSIP0035=CWSIP0035E: An attempt to attach a consumer to the subscription {0} on the remote messaging engine {1} failed as the subscription is already homed locally.
Message.Explanation: A durable subscription can only live on one messaging engine. A subscription with a similar name is currently homed on the local ME, so it cannot be homed on the remote ME.
Message.UserResponse: Change the durable subscription home property of the durable subscription or delete the local subscription.

Message.MsgText: CONSUMER_NOT_BIFURCATABLE_CWSIP0680=CWSIP0680E: Unable to create a bifurcated consumer from consumer {0}, consumer {0} is not bifurcatable.
Message.Explanation: Bifurcated consumers can only be created from consumers that were initially created as bifurcatable.
Message.UserResponse: Change the application that create the consumer to allow bifuracted consumers to be created.

Message.MsgText: ANYCAST_CANNOT_REQUEST_FLUSH_CWSIP0518=CWSIP0518E: Cannot attach to queue point for destination {0} on messaging engine {1}..
Message.Explanation: The messaging engine hosting the queue point for the destination is unreachable.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that the messaging engine has been started and communications are active between messaging engines before retrying the operation.

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_CHANGE_REASON_ADMIN_ACTION_SIMP0771=CWSIP0771I: Administrator action.
Message.Explanation: The mediation point entered a state as a result of an action by the administrator.
Message.UserResponse: Refer to the documentation to discover how to change the state of the mediation point if required.

Message.MsgText: MORE_THAN_ONE_ME_CONTROL_LISTENER_CWSIP0853=CWSIP0853W: Found {0} registered MessagingEngineControlListeners but there should be only one. The listeners found were {1}
Message.Explanation: Only one listener may be registered. The system will utilise only the first MessagingEngineControlListener in the list.
Message.UserResponse: Specify only one MessagingEngineControlListener

Message.MsgText: LOCAL_DEST_DELETE_INFO_CWSIP0063=CWSIP0063I: The local destination {0} with UUID {1} has been marked for deletion.

Message.MsgText: MISSING_PARAM_ERROR_CWSIP0044=CWSIP0044W: An internal messaging error occurred. The destinationName has not been supplied on messaging engine {0}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.

Message.MsgText: REMOTE_DEST_DELETE_INFO_CWSIP0066=CWSIP0066I: The remote destination {0} with UUID {1} has been marked for deletion.
Message.Explanation: The WCCM configuration for this destination on a remote messaging engine has been removed, so its resources will be scheduled for deletion.

Message.MsgText: TEMPORARY_DESTINATION_CONNECTION_ERROR_CWSIP0099=CWSIP0099E: The temporary destination with name {0} cannot be found because the temporary destination was created on a different connection.
Message.Explanation: Temporary destinations can be accessed from the same connection only.

Message.MsgText: UNRESOLVED_GAP_IN_LINK_TRANSMITTER_CWSIP0790=CWSIP0790W: Messaging engine {3} has detected a gap in the stream of messages received from bus {1} on link {2}. Requests made to fill this gap have yet to be satisfied. The gap starts at sequence id {0}.
Message.Explanation: The messaging engine receiving messages over the inter-bus link has detected a gap in the sequence ids of messages received. Requests for re-delivery of one or more messages have been made to the sending messaging engine but the gap has not yet been filled. If the inter-bus link is not currently running, the gap will not be resolved until the inter-bus link is restarted.
Message.UserResponse: Restart the link if it is stopped.

Message.MsgText: USER_NOT_AUTH_INQUIRE_FB_ERROR_CWSIP0315=CWSIP0315E: Inquire access for foreign bus {0} was denied for user with subject {1}
Message.Explanation: A user is not authorized to inquire about the configuration for the specified Foreign Bus
Message.UserResponse: If the user should have access to inquire about the configuration of the Foreign Bus, edit the Inquire access control in the adminstration console by adding the specified user

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_CHANGE_REASON_WAIT_DELETE_SIMP0775=CWSIP0775I: Waiting for the deletion of another mediation point on this destination.
Message.Explanation: The mediation point has been added to the destination before the previous mediation point instance has been completely removed. The mediation will wait until the removal of the previous mediation is complete before it can continue.
Message.UserResponse: Refer to the documentation to discover how to change the state of the mediation point if required.

Message.MsgText: CLONED_SUBSCRIBER_OVERRIDE_CWSIP0028=CWSIP0028W: Support for multiple subscribers to subscription {0}, on destination {1}, has been disabled.
Message.Explanation: The destination is set to maintain message ordering. Therefore any subscriptions on the destination can only have one subscriber.

Message.MsgText: MISSING_PARAM_ERROR_CWSIP0029=CWSIP0029W: An internal messaging error occurred. The parameter with name mqLinkUuidStr has not been supplied at location {0}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: FLUSH_REQUESTED_MESSAGE_CWSIP0780=CWSIP0780I: Messaging engine: {0} started, flush of all delivery streams requested.

Message.MsgText: RMQ_INTERNAL_ERROR_CWSIP0820=CWSIP0820W: An internal messaging error occurred when using the Websphere MQ Server bus member {0} : {1}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: LINK_ALREADY_EXISTS_ERROR_CWSIP0043=CWSIP0043E: The link with name {0} already exists on messaging engine {1}.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to create a link, but the named link already exists on the named messaging engine.

Message.MsgText: MESSAGE_CORRUPT_ERROR_CWSIP0262=CWSIP0262E: The current message is corrupt and can not be added to the persistent store due to exception {0}
Message.Explanation: Messages are added to the Persistent Store, but this failed due to a problem being encountered.
Message.UserResponse: Check the linked exception and correct any problems before resending the message

Message.MsgText: USER_NOT_AUTH_CREATE_ERROR_CWSIP0305=CWSIP0305E: The user with subject {1} is not authorized to create temporary destinations with prefix {0}.
Message.Explanation: A user is not authorized to create temporary destinations with the named prefix.
Message.UserResponse: If the user should have authority to create temporary destinations with the named prefix then update the users authorization rights for the named prefix.

Message.MsgText: MESSAGE_HANDLER_CORRUPT_ERROR_CWSIP0201=CWSIP0201E: This operation is not available
Message.Explanation: This message handler is corrupt or is in reset state.
Message.UserResponse: Reset the message handler if it is not already in reset state. Then restart the messaging engine.

Message.MsgText: ASYNCH_CONSUMER_RUN_ERROR_CWSIP0176=CWSIP0176E: An asynchronous consumer cannot be registered on destination {0}, messaging engine {1} when the session is started.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to register an asynchronous consumer on a destination when the session used to create the consumer is not in a stopped state.
Message.UserResponse: Stop the consumer and try again.

Message.MsgText: USER_NOT_AUTH_EXCEPTION_DEST_ERROR_CWSIP0313=CWSIP0313E: A user {0} is not authorized to access exception destination {1}.
Message.Explanation: A user is not authorized to put messages to the Exception destination specified.
Message.UserResponse: If the user should have access to the exception destination, edit the exception destination access control in the adminstration console by adding the specified user

Message.MsgText: TRANSACTION_DELETE_USAGE_ERROR_CWSIP0778=CWSIP0778E: The transaction used for delete on the destination: {0} has already been completed.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to use a transaction that has already been completed.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the transaction used is a new transaction.

Message.MsgText: FLUSH_FAILED_MESSAGE_CWSIP0782=CWSIP0782E: Messaging engine: {0} started, flush of stream: {1} and destination: {2} failed with the exception: {3}.
Message.Explanation: An error has occurred while flushing the streams.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, contact your IBM Support representative.

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_CHANGE_REASON_WAIT_WAS_SIMP0774=CWSIP0774I: Waiting for WebSphere server to start
Message.Explanation: The mediation point entered a state while waiting for the Websphere Server to start.
Message.UserResponse: Refer to the documentation to discover how to change the state of the mediation point if required.

Message.MsgText: OBJECT_CLOSED_ERROR_CWSIP0081=CWSIP0081E: Browser Session is closed on destination {0} and cannot be used.
Message.Explanation: The browser has been closed and cannot be used on the specified destination.

Message.MsgText: MSGSTORE_STOP_RETRY_CWSIP0457=CWSIP0457E: Failed to persist state for remote consumer access for destination {0} that is localised at this ME.
Message.Explanation: The local state for remotely attached consumers to the destination may be corrupt because a local transaction failed to commit after many retries.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: INVALID_PARAMETER_COMBINATION_ERROR_CWSIP0100=CWSIP0100E: The supplied parameter combination is not valid for the creation of cloned durable subscription {0} on destination {1} for messaging engine {2}

Message.MsgText: REPORT_MESSAGE_ERROR_CWSIP0423=CWSIP0423E: A requested Confirm on Delivery report message type could not be sent on messaging engine {0}. {1}
Message.Explanation: A problem occurred generating a Confirm on delivery report message type.

Message.MsgText: REPORT_MESSAGE_ERROR_CWSIP0422=CWSIP0422E: A requested expiry report message type could not be sent on messaging engine {0}. {1}

Message.UserResponse: Correct any associated errors. If problems persist, contact your IBM Support representative.

Message.Explanation: Service destinations cannot have Browsers attached to them. An exception is created for any attempt to create a Browser session to a Service destination

Message.Explanation: Service destinations cannot have Consumers attached to them. An exception is created for any attempt to create a consumer session to a Service destination
Message.UserResponse: Create a destination which is not a Service destination and create a Consumer against this destination.

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_STOPPED_BY_FAILURE_TO_MOVE_UNMEDIATED_MESSAGE_SIMP0662=CWSIP0662E: The mediation point for destination {0} attempted to move a message to the post-mediated side of the destination. This operation failed.
Message.Explanation: The message was not put to the post-mediated side of the destination. The mediation point has been stopped.
Message.UserResponse: The mediation can retry moving the message when it has been restarted.

Message.MsgText: MQLINK_DEST_DELETE_INFO_CWSIP0064=CWSIP0064I: The WebSphere MQ link {0} with UUID {1} has been marked for deletion.
Message.Explanation: The WCCM configuration for this WebSphere MQ link on this messaging engine has been removed, so its resources will be scheduled for deletion.
Message.UserResponse: none

Message.MsgText: DESTINATION_IS_LOCKED_ERROR_CWSIP0133=CWSIP0133E: An attempt was made to open destination {0} on messaging engine {1} for Consuming. The destination is temporarily locked.

Message.UserResponse: Try again.

Message.MsgText: LINK_HANDLER_RECOVERY_ERROR_CWSIP0049=CWSIP0049E: The Link {0} cannot be recovered from data store.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_MSG_NOT_SENT_CWSIP0812=CWSIP0812W: A message could not be sent to the mediation point associated with destination {0} associated with the WebSphere MQ Server bus member {1}. The WebSphere MQ completion code was {2}. The WebSphere MQ reason code was {3}.

Message.MsgText: SUBSCRIPTION_NOT_FOUND_ERROR_CWSIP0271=CWSIP0271E: Subscription with id {0} not found
Message.Explanation: Attaching at Runtime to a subscription failed as the subscription could not be found. This could have been caused by the subscription being deleted.
Message.UserResponse: Reconnect using the Administrative Console to another subscription to view the state

Message.MsgText: NOTIFY_MEDIATION_STATE_CHANGE_CWSIP0657=CWSIP0657I: The local mediation point for destination {0} and mediation {1} has moved to state {2}.
Message.Explanation: The mediation point has moved to a new state.
Message.UserResponse: none.

Message.MsgText: SYSTEM_DESTINATION_USAGE_ERROR_CWSIP0024=CWSIP0024E: An attempt was made to access a non system destination {0} from a system connection on messaging engine {1}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: INVALID_TOPIC_ERROR_CWSIP0372=CWSIP0372E: The topic syntax {0} is not valid.
Message.Explanation: The topic syntax supplied is not valid.

Message.MsgText: USER_NOT_AUTHORIZED_ERROR_CWSIP0302=CWSIP0302E: A user {0} is not authorized to access the messaging engine {1} on bus {2}.
Message.Explanation: The user specified is not authorized to access the messaging engine bus.

Message.MsgText: USER_NOT_AUTHORIZED_ERROR_CWSIP0301=CWSIP0301E: Unable to authenticate user {0} when creating a connection to secure messaging engine {1} on bus {2}.
Message.Explanation: The user specified could not be authenticated when trying to create a connection to the messaging engine bus
Message.UserResponse: Check the user has been added to the WebSphere Application Server security repository and that the correct password has been specified

Message.MsgText: REMOTE_DESTINATION_DEPTH_INTERVAL_REACHED_CWSIP0788=CWSIP0788I: {0} messages queued on messaging engine {1} for transmission to destination {2} on messaging engine {3}.
Message.Explanation: The remote message point for the destination has reached the stated message depth
Message.UserResponse: No action to be taken.

Message.MsgText: FLUSH_COMPLETED_MESSAGE_CWSIP0783=CWSIP0783I: Messaging engine: {0} started, flush of all delivery streams completed.

Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: DESTINATION_DELETED_ERROR_CWSIP0247=CWSIP0247E: The destination {0} has been deleted and the message cannot be put to the exception destination do to reason {1}.
Message.Explanation: An attempt to commit a message on a deleted destination resulted in an error.

Message.MsgText: CORE_MESSAGE_NOT_FOUND_ERROR_CWSIP0173=CWSIP0173E: Unable to locate message {0} on destination {1} on messaging engine {2}
Message.Explanation: A request was made to locate a message on a destination, but the message does not exist.
Message.UserResponse: The message may have previously been deleted, or expired. Check that the message exists on the specified destination and retry the operation.

Message.MsgText: FAILED_XA_CONNECTION_CWSIP0821=CWSIP0821W: Failed to create a connection from resource manager, {0}, to Messaging Engine {1} on bus {2} when retrieving a transaction.
Message.Explanation: An internal connection to a messaging engine could not be created and will be retried at a later time.
Message.UserResponse: none

Message.MsgText: USER_NOT_AUTH_RECEIVE_ERROR_CWSIP0310=CWSIP0310E: Receive access from discriminator {1} on destination {0} was denied for user with subject {2}.
Message.Explanation: A user is not authorized to receive from the destination using the specified topic.
Message.UserResponse: If the user should have authority to receive messages on the given topic then update the users authorization rights for the topic on the given destination.

Message.MsgText: NO_NEIGHBOUR_REPLY_WARNING_CWSIP0381=CWSIP0381W: No Response received from messaging engine {0} for subscription request message.

Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the remote messaging engine listed is started. If the problem persists, contact your IBM Support representative.

Message.MsgText: MAX_BATCH_SIZE_OVERRIDE_WARNING_CWSIP0181=CWSIP0181W: The maximum batch size for the consumer on destination {0}, has been set to 1.
Message.Explanation: The destination is set to maintain message ordering. Therefore the maximum batch size for a consumer has been set to 1.

Message.MsgText: MSG_NOT_SENT_CWSIP0811=CWSIP0811W: A message could not be sent to destination {0} assigned to WebSphere MQ Server bus member {1}. The WebSphere MQ completion code was {2}. The WebSphere MQ reason code was {3}.

Message.UserResponse: Consult the WebSphere MQ documentation to determine the meaning of the completion and reason codes. Perform the appropriate corrective action.

Message.MsgText: USER_NOT_AUTH_RECEIVE_ERROR_CWSIP0309=CWSIP0309E: Receive access from destination {0} was denied for user with subject {1}.

Message.MsgText: DELETE_SYSTEM_DEST_ERROR_CWSIP0046=CWSIP0046W: An internal messaging error occurred. Unable to delete system destination {0} on messaging engine {1}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.

Message.MsgText: CONSUMER_CLOSED_ERROR_CWSIP0177=CWSIP0177E: The consumer session on destination {0} on messaging engine {1} has been closed.
Message.Explanation: An operation cannot be performed on the consumer session when it has been closed.

Message.MsgText: CONSUMERCARDINALITY_LIMIT_REACHED_CWSIP0472=CWSIP0472E: The consumer attach is not being permitted or it is being detached because the consumer cardinality limit for destination {0} localised at ME {1} has been reached.

Message.MsgText: DESTINATION_HIGH_MESSAGES_ERROR_CWSIP0251=CWSIP0251E: The destination {0} on messaging engine {2} is not available because the high limit {1} for the number of messages for this destination has already been reached.

Message.UserResponse: Check that the configured high messages limit for the destination is correct.

Message.MsgText: RECEIVE_USAGE_ERROR_CWSIP0178=CWSIP0178E: The receive operation is not valid at this time on destination {0} on messaging engine {1}.

Message.UserResponse: Allow the original receive operation to complete and try again.

Message.MsgText: RECEIVE_USAGE_ERROR_CWSIP0174=CWSIP0174E: An asynchronous consumer cannot be registered on destination {0} on messaging engine {1} when issuing a synchronous receive command.

Message.UserResponse: Make sure the consumer is not registered as an asynchronous consumer and try again.

Message.MsgText: INTERNAL_SUBSCRIPTION_TARGET_NOT_FOUND_CWSIP0115=CWSIP0115E: A message matched to subscription {0} on messaging engine {1} could not be sent to destination {2} because the destination could not be found.

Message.UserResponse: The destination may not exist or has been deleted. Check that the destination exists and is accessible.

Message.MsgText: NULL_DESTINATIONADDRESS_CWSIP0668=CWSIP0668E: An internal error occurred. The destinationAddress command failed because the ConsumerSetChangeCallback parameter passed is Null.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.

Message.MsgText: GATHERING_ME_VERSION_INCOMPATIBLE_CWSIP0856=CWSIP0856E: Cannot attach to queue point for destination {0} on messaging engine {1} for message gathering as the messaging engine is the wrong version.
Message.Explanation: The messaging engine hosting the queue point for the destination is an older version and does not support message gathering.
Message.UserResponse: Either use a non-gathering consumer or migrate the hosting messaging engine to a new product version.

Message.MsgText: INTERNAL_SUBSCRIPTION_ACCESS_DISALLOWED_CWSIP0147=CWSIP0147E: The durable subscription with name {0} on messaging engine {1} is an internal subscription and therefore cannot be attached to.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to access a durable subscription, but this durable subscription is internal and cannot be used.
Message.UserResponse: An Internal Subscription is used to map publications to a target destination. Internal subscription cannot be attached to by external consumers. Retry using a valid subscription name.

Message.MsgText: ACL_ADD_WARNING_CWSIP0375=CWSIP0375W: Unable to load access control list to due to exception {1} for discriminator {0}
Message.Explanation: When the access control list was loaded an exception occurred.
Message.UserResponse: Check and correct the related exception to enable the access control list to load correctly.

Message.MsgText: ACL_ADD_WARNING_CWSIP0374=CWSIP0374W: Unable to load access control list to due to exception {2} for discriminator {0} and user {1}
Message.Explanation: When the access control list was loaded an exception occurred.
Message.UserResponse: Check and correct the related exception to enable the access control list to load correctly.

Message.MsgText: ACL_ADD_WARNING_CWSIP0373=CWSIP0373W: Unable to load access control list to due to exception {0}.
Message.Explanation: When the access control list was loaded an exception occurred.
Message.UserResponse: Check and correct the related exception to enable the access control list to load correctly.

Message.MsgText: ORDERING_INITIALISATION_ERROR_CWSIP0671=CWSIP0671E: The destination {0} on messaging engine {1} failed to be inititialised for maintaining order.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to initialise an ordered destination but the destination had multiple outstanding transactions.
Message.UserResponse: Complete all transactions on the destination before ordering can be activated.

Message.MsgText: MESSAGE_LOCK_EXPIRED_ERROR_CWSIP0193=CWSIP0193E: The lock has expired for message with id {0} on messaging engine {1}.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to use a message inside a Consumer, but the lock timeout has expired and the message was made reavailable.
Message.UserResponse: When a lock expires the message is made reavailable for another Consumer to process.

Message.MsgText: STREAM_BLOCKED_BY_COMMITTING_MESSAGE_CWSIP0785=CWSIP0785W: A message held on messaging engine {1} for transmission to a remote destination or foreign bus {0} has remained in committing state for {2} seconds under transaction {3}. Further messages may not flow until this transaction completes.
Message.Explanation: Any messages for the remote destination or foreign bus sent after the blocked message will not be transmitted until the transaction is resolved.
Message.UserResponse: Resolve the transaction identified as blocking the message

Message.MsgText: EXCEPTION_CWSIP0813=CWSIP0813W: An exception {0} occurred when attempting to send a message to destination {1} assigned to WebSphere MQ Server bus member {2}.
Message.Explanation: A message could not be sent to the specified destination, assigned to the specified WebSphere MQ Server bus member. The WebSphere exception specified may be used to determine why the message could not be sent.
Message.UserResponse: Consult the WebSphere MQ documentation to determine the meaning of the exception. Perform the appropriate corrective action.

Message.MsgText: NOTIFY_SIBLINK_DEPTH_THRESHOLD_REACHED_CWSIP0560=CWSIP0560W: The link {0} for bus {1}, on ME {2} has reached its message depth low threshold.
Message.Explanation: The number of messages stored at a Link has made a depth change that takes the number stored below the depth low threshold.
Message.UserResponse: None.

Message.MsgText: NULL_CONSUMERSETCHANGECALLBACK_CWSIP0667=CWSIP0667E: An internal error occurred. The registerConsumerSetMonitor command failed because the ConsumerSetChangeCallback parameter passed is Null.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_FAILED_TO_START_SIMP0655=CWSIP0655E: The local mediation point for destination {0} failed to start because an error occurred. Mediation {1} was not found. The error is {2}.
Message.Explanation: The mediation point remains in the stopped state.
Message.UserResponse: The mediation point can be restarted once the conditions for the error have been changed.

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_FAILED_TO_START_SIMP0654=CWSIP0654E: The local mediation point for destination {0} failed to start because an error occurred. The mediation definition is incorrect. The error is {1}.
Message.Explanation: The mediation point remains in the stopped state.
Message.UserResponse: The mediation point can be restarted once the conditions for the error have been changed.

Message.MsgText: NOTIFY_SIBLINK_DEPTH_THRESHOLD_REACHED_CWSIP0559=CWSIP0559W: The link {0} for bus {1}, on ME {2} has reached its message depth high threshold.
Message.Explanation: The number of messages stored at a Link has made a depth change that takes the number stored over the depth high threshold.
Message.UserResponse: None.

Message.MsgText: MSG_BLOCK_WARNING_CWSIP0182=CWSIP0182W: Consumer {0} of resource {1} on messaging engine {2} has been blocked for {3} seconds.
Message.Explanation: The message consumer on the named resource has been blocked for an unexpectedly long period of time, processing the same set of messages. While in this state it is unable to process any further messages.
Message.UserResponse: Resolve why the message consumer has become blocked, investigate the state of the applications currently consuming messages from the resource.

Message.MsgText: DESTINATION_DELETED_ERROR_CWSIP0550=CWSIP0550E: The destination {0}, UUID {1} has been deleted and the message cannot be put to the exception destination.
Message.Explanation: An attempt to clean up the messages on the specified destination resulted in an error.
Message.UserResponse: The clean-up will be retried at a later time.

Message.MsgText: NULL_DISCRIMINATOREXPRESSION_CWSIP0669=CWSIP0669E: An internal error occurred. The discriminatorExpression command failed because the ConsumerSetChangeCallback parameter passed is Null.
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: MESSAGE_PROCESSOR_NOT_STARTED_ERROR_CWSIP0211=CWSIP0211E: Messaging engine {0} on bus {1} is not started.
Message.Explanation: A request was made to access the named messaging engine, but it has not been started
Message.UserResponse: Start the named messaging engine .

Message.MsgText: FLUSH_COMPLETE_CWSIP0452=CWSIP0452I: Force flush completed for Anycast stream for destination {0} that is localised on messaging engine {1} since remote ME {2} has been deleted
Message.Explanation: None
Message.UserResponse: None

Message.MsgText: FLUSH_COMPLETE_CWSIP0451=CWSIP0451I: Force flush completed for Anycast streams for the given ME {0} and destination {1} that is localised here
Message.Explanation: None
Message.UserResponse: None

Message.MsgText: NOTIFY_RECEIVE_ALLOWED_STATE_CHANGE_CWSIP0552=CWSIP0552I: The receive allowed state of destination {0}, with UUID {1} has changed to {2}.
Message.Explanation: The behaviour of the message points associated with the destination has been altered.
Message.UserResponse: None.

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_POINT_DELETED_ERROR_SIMP0641=CWSIP0641E: The local mediation point for destination {0} has been deleted and the message cannot be put to the exception destination.
Message.Explanation: An attempt to move the messages from the deleted local mediation point of the destination resulted in an error.
Message.UserResponse: The clean-up will be retried at a later time.

Message.MsgText: CONNECTION_CONTROLLABLE_ERROR_CWSIP0571=CWSIP0571E: The connection object no longer exists.
Message.Explanation: An Attempt to access a Connection failed as the Connection no longer exists. This could be due to an application closing the connection.
Message.UserResponse: None

Message.MsgText: DESTINATION_SEND_DISALLOWED_CWSIP0253=CWSIP0253E: The destination {0} is send disallowed for messaging engine {1}
Message.Explanation: An attempt has been made to send a message to a destination and a check has been made to ensure that a publication point is available for this destination. This check failed as the publication point for this destination is send disallowed.
Message.UserResponse: Update the publication point for the destination so it is send allowed and retry the send operation.

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_EXCEPTION_MSG_NOT_RECEIVED_CWSIP0818=CWSIP0818W: An exception {0} occurred when attempting to receive a message from the mediation point associated with destination {1} assigned to WebSphere MQ Server bus member {2}.
Message.Explanation: A message could not be received from the mediation point associated with the specified destination, assigned to the specified WebSphere MQ Server. The WebSphere exception specified may be used to determine why the message could not be received.
Message.UserResponse: Consult the WebSphere MQ documentation to determine the meaning of the exception. Perform the appropriate corrective action.

Message.MsgText: SUBSCRIPTION_IN_USE_ERROR_CWSIP0153=CWSIP0153E: The durable subscription with name {0} has messages that are uncommitted on messaging engine {1}.
Message.Explanation: A durable subscription has messages that are uncommitted so the attempt to delete failed.
Message.UserResponse: Commit any outstanding units of work created by either been sending to or receiving from the durable subscription consuming application, then try again.

Message.MsgText: SUBSCRIPTION_IN_USE_ERROR_CWSIP0152=CWSIP0152E: The durable subscription with name {0} is in use by another consumer on messaging engine {1}.
Message.Explanation: A durable subscription with the specified name is in use by another consumer. Operations cannot be performed on the subscription until all consumers have disconnected.
Message.UserResponse: Only a single consumer is allowed to attach to a durable subscription. Detach any consumers and try again.

Message.MsgText: SUBSCRIPTION_ALREADY_EXISTS_ERROR_CWSIP0143=CWSIP0143E: The subscription with name {0} already exists on messaging engine {1}.
Message.Explanation: An attempt to create a durable subscription was made with the given name, but this subscription already exists.
Message.UserResponse: Delete the existing subscription and try again, or create the subscription with a new name.

Message.MsgText: DESTINATION_UNREACHABLE_ERROR_CWSIP00223=CWSIP0223E: The destination with name {0} on messaging engine {1} has a message point which cannot be reached.
Message.Explanation: An application that was connected to the specified destination has been disconnected as the messaging engine localising the destination could not be reached.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the messaging engine localising the destination is available.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_DEST_ALTER_ERROR_CWSIP0045=CWSIP0045W: An internal messaging error occurred. An invalid destination alter command was supplied for destination {0} on messaging engine {1}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: TRANSACTION_RECEIVE_USAGE_ERROR_CWSIP0777=CWSIP0777E: The transaction used for receive on the destination: {0} has already been completed.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to use a transaction that has already been completed.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the transaction used is a new transaction.

Message.MsgText: DESTINATION_DEPTH_INTERVAL_REACHED_CWSIP0787=CWSIP0787I: Destination {0} on messaging engine {1} has reached a depth of {2} messages.
Message.Explanation: The message point for the destination has reached the stated message depth
Message.UserResponse: No action to be taken.

Message.MsgText: ORDERED_MESSAGING_ERROR_CWSIP0194=CWSIP0194E: The destination with name {0} on messaging engine {1} is unavailable for receiving messages due to a current transacted receive taking place.
Message.Explanation: An attempt has been made to receive messages from a destination when it is configured with ordering maintained. Another transaction is currently outstanding on this destination.
Message.UserResponse: Complete all other transactions on this destination before attempting to receive with a new transaction.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_RECONSTITUTE_THREADPOOL_SIZE_CWSIP0069=CWSIP0069W: Reconstitute Thread Pool Size is greater than numberOfCores.
Message.Explanation: Reconstitute Thread Pool Size is greater than numberOfCores.
Message.UserResponse: none

Message.MsgText: INVALID_RECONSTITUTE_THREADPOOL_SIZE_CWSIP0068=CWSIP0068I: Invalid Reconstitute ThreadPool size : {0}
Message.Explanation: Invalid Reconstitute ThreadPool size provided in the custom property sib.processor.maxReconstituteThreadpoolSize
Message.UserResponse: Change the value of the custom property sib.processor.maxReconstituteThreadpoolSize to a valid value.

Message.MsgText: UNRESOLVED_GAP_IN_DESTINATION_TRANSMITTER_CWSIP0792=CWSIP0792W: Messaging engine {3} has detected a gap in the stream of messages received from messaging engine {2} for destination {1}. Requests made to fill this gap have yet to be satisfied. The gap starts at sequence id {0}.
Message.Explanation: The messaging engine receiving messages for the destination has detected a gap in the sequence ids of messages received. Requests for re-delivery of one or more messages have been made to the sending messaging engine but the gap has not yet been filled. If the messaging engines are unable to communicate the gap will not be resolved until this is resolved.
Message.UserResponse: Restart the sending messaging engine if it is stopped and ensure the connection between the two messaging engines is active.

Message.MsgText: SUBSCRIPTION_DOESNT_EXIST_ERROR_CWSIP0146=CWSIP0146E: The durable subscription with name {0} does not exist on messaging engine {1}.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to access a durable subscription, but this durable subscription doesn't exist.
Message.UserResponse: The subscription may have been deleted or not yet created. Check that the subscription exists and retry the command.

Message.MsgText: REMOTE_ME_MAPPING_ERROR_CWSIP0156=CWSIP0156E: An error occurred while locating the remote messaging engine {0}.
Message.Explanation: Processing could not be completed because the remote messaging engine could not be found.
Message.UserResponse: Verify that messaging engine name is valid and the Remote messaging engine is running and that communications between messaging engine are active.

Message.MsgText: DESTINATION_INDOUBT_ERROR_CWSIP0062=CWSIP0062E: The destination {0} with UUID {1} could not be recovered due to a possible WCCM configuration error
Message.Explanation: The WCCM configuration for this destination on this messaging engine has become incorrect, so the destination will not be made available on this messaging engine.
Message.UserResponse: Correct the WCCM configuration and then restart the server. The destination will then be made available again on this messaging engine.

Message.MsgText: BROWSE_FAILED_CWSIP0533=CWSIP0533E: A remote browse of destination {0} failed with reason: {1}
Message.Explanation: The messaging engine hosting a message point for the destination returned an error code during a browse request.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: MSG_NOT_RECEIVED_CWSIP0815=CWSIP0815W: A message could not be received from destination {0} assigned to WebSphere MQ Server bus member {1}. The WebSphere MQ completion code was {2}. The WebSphere MQ reason code was {3}.
Message.Explanation: A message could not be received from the specified destination, assigned to the specified WebSphere MQ Server bus member. The WebSphere MQ completion and reason codes specified can be used to determine why the message could not be received.
Message.UserResponse: Consult the WebSphere MQ documentation to determine the meaning of the completion and reason codes. Perform the appropriate corrective action.

Message.MsgText: DESTINATION_DELETE_ERROR_CWSIP0331=CWSIP0331W: The destination {0} on messaging engine {1} has already been marked for deletion.
Message.Explanation: A request has been made to delete a destination, but this destination has already been marked for deletion.
Message.UserResponse: The destination should be removed from the messaging engine by the system.

Message.MsgText: LINK_HANDLER_WARM_START_ERROR_CWSIP0056=CWSIP0056E: The link with name {0} and UUID {1} cannot be recovered from data store. {2}
Message.Explanation: This exception is unexpected. The cause is not immediately known.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: ORDERED_DESTINATION_IN_USE_CWSIP0116=CWSIP0116E: The destination with name {0} on messaging engine {1} is ordered and already has a consumer attached
Message.Explanation: An attempt has been made to create a consumer session to a destination configured with ordering maintained. This operation has failed because a consumer is already attached to the destination.
Message.UserResponse: Detach all other consumers before attempting to reattach.

Message.MsgText: ENCODE_FAIL_ERROR_CWSIP0281=CWSIP0281E: Failed to encode message for transmit to remote messaging engine {0} on destination {1} with value {2}, {3} and error {4}
Message.Explanation: A message that is bound for a remote messaging engine failed to be encoded and could not be sent
Message.UserResponse: Check the ffdc logs for the reason the message failed to encode and correct the error. The current message needs to be removed from the outbound stream. This can be done removing from the Remote Queue Point using the Administrative Console.

Message.MsgText: FLUSH_INITIATED_MESSAGE_CWSIP0781=CWSIP0781I: Messaging engine: {0} started, flush initiated for stream: {1} and destination: {2}.
Message.Explanation: The messaging engine has begun its flushing of the stream.
Message.UserResponse: None.

Message.MsgText: ALIAS_CIRCULAR_DEPENDENCY_ERROR_CWSIP0621=CWSIP0621E: An error occurred while resolving the alias destination {0} due to the following circular dependency {1} on messaging engine bus {2}
Message.Explanation: The alias destination could not be resolved due to a circular dependency
Message.UserResponse: Break the circular dependency by changing aliases in the resolution path in the administrative console.

Message.MsgText: HEALTHSTATE_STATUS_CWSIP0920=CWSIP0920I: Status OK
Message.Explanation: No problems have been detected with message transmission
Message.UserResponse: none

Message.MsgText: EXCEPTION_DESTINATION_WARNING_CWSIP0291=CWSIP0291W: An attempt to send a message to exception destination {0} on messaging engine {1} failed due to the following : {2}
Message.Explanation: An attempt to send a message to the specified exception destination failed. This will be retried using the default exception destination.
Message.UserResponse: Check that the specified destination exists and that it is operational.

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_CHANGE_REASON_CONFIG_CHANGE_SIMP0776=CWSIP0776I: Applying a configuration change.
Message.Explanation: The mediation point has entered this state as a result of a change in the configuration.
Message.UserResponse: Refer to the documentation to discover how to change the state of the mediation point if required.

Message.MsgText: FORWARD_ROUTING_PATH_ERROR_CWSIP0249=CWSIP0249E: A message could not be delivered to a destination in the forward routing path as destination {0} is a topic space on messaging engine {1}
Message.Explanation: A forward routing path contained a topic space, which was not the final element in the path. Any following destinations cannot be delivered to.
Message.UserResponse: A topic space can only be the final element in a forward routing path. Correct the path and retry.

Message.MsgText: HEALTHSTATE_STATUS_CWSIP0919=CWSIP0919W: Blocked receiver, the receiver cannot deliver the current inbound message for reason {0} on destination {1}
Message.Explanation: The reciever is unable to deliver a message to the target destination for the given reason, until this problem is resolved delivery of subsequent messages will be blocked.
Message.UserResponse: If this state persists take appropriate action to resolve the problem with the message.

Message.MsgText: HEALTHSTATE_STATUS_CWSIP0917=CWSIP0917W: Re-establishing message delivery
Message.Explanation: A break in message transmission has been observed and is being resolved, possibly due to a break in communication or the rate of message production has exceeded the capability to receive them.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the messaging engines that are communicating are active and have a network connection between them. If this state persists reduce the rate of message production if appropriate or check the system logs for errors.

Message.MsgText: HEALTHSTATE_STATUS_CWSIP0916=CWSIP0916W: Inefficient message delivery has been observed, due to re-delivering messages.
Message.Explanation: Re-delivery of messages is acceptable but not efficient. Possible reasons for requiring re-delivery are that the connection with the source messaging engine is lost or intermittent, or the rate of message production is exceeding the capability to receive them.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the messaging engines that are communicating are active and have a network connection between them. If this state persists reduce the rate of message production if appropriate or check the system logs for errors.

Message.MsgText: HEALTHSTATE_STATUS_CWSIP0914=CWSIP0914W: Inefficient message delivery has been observed, due to re-delivering messages.
Message.Explanation: One or more messages have required re-delivery to the receiving messaging engine, this is acceptable but not efficient. Possible reasons for requiring re-delivery are when the connection with the target messaging engine is lost or intermittent, or the rate of message production is exceeding the capability to transmit them.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the messaging engines that are communicating are active and have a network connection between them. If this state persists reduce the rate of message production if appropriate or check the system logs for errors.

Message.MsgText: HEALTHSTATE_STATUS_CWSIP0913=CWSIP0913W: Full message transmitter
Message.Explanation: The message transmitter has reached the messaging engine's high message threshold. The message backlog may be due to the receiving messaging engine not currently accepting messages or the rate of message production exceeding the capability to transmit the messages.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the messaging engines that are communicating are active and have a network connection between them. If this state persists reduce the rate of message production if appropriate or check the system logs for errors.

Message.MsgText: HEALTHSTATE_STATUS_CWSIP0912=CWSIP0912W: Blocked transmitter, the lead message has been held under an in-doubt transaction for an unexpectedly long period
Message.Explanation: The message at the front of the transmission stream is partially committed, the transaction is potentially in-doubt. The remaining messages will be blocked until the transaction is resolved.
Message.UserResponse: Locate the blocked message and diagnose the reason for the identified transaction being in this state. Resolving the transaction will unblock the messages

Message.MsgText: HEALTHSTATE_STATUS_CWSIP0911=CWSIP0911W: No response from receiver, acknowledgement of sent messages are overdue
Message.Explanation: Messages have been sent to a remote messaging engine but no acknowledgment has been received for those messages for an unexpectedly long period of time.
Message.UserResponse: Ensure that the receiving messaging engine is started and able to communicate with the sending messaging engine. If it is then the system may be overloaded at this time and a reduction of message traffic will cure the problem.

Message.MsgText: PROXY_LIMIT_EXCEEDED_WARNING_CWSIP0036=CWSIP0036E: An attempt to send a control message to an internal system destination {0} destination for messaging engine {1} has failed as the destination is full.
Message.Explanation: A control message cannot be sent to the destination as the destination is full. This means that the Publish Subscribe topology is now inconsistent.
Message.UserResponse: Clear the messages from the system destination and restart the server. Ensure that the remote messaging engine is started and communications have been established between them.

Message.MsgText: HEALTHSTATE_STATUS_CWSIP0908=CWSIP0908E: Error detected ({0})
Message.Explanation: One or more errors have been detected that may prevent further messages from being transmitted or received. Check the system logs for errors.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: HEALTHSTATE_STATUS_CWSIP0905=CWSIP0905W: No connection established
Message.Explanation: The connection between this messaging engine and the foreign bus is not currently available, possibly due to the link not being started or the messaging engine unable to communicate with the messaging engine in the foreign bus
Message.UserResponse: Ensure the link is started and the messaging engines that host the link are active and have a working network connection between them.

Message.MsgText: CREATE_CONSUMER_ERROR_CWSIP0092=CWSIP0092E: Unable to create BifurcatedConsumer to original consumer {0} on messaging engine {1}.
Message.Explanation: An attempt was made to create a BifurcatedConsumer, but the originating consumer was not found with the identifier supplied.
Message.UserResponse: Make sure that the originating consumer is active and retry the operation with the correct identifier.

Message.MsgText: INVALID_FLOW_CLASSIFICATIONS_CWSIP0852=CWSIP0852E: The setFlowProperties command failed on Consumer Set {0} because invalid Message Classification Flows were specified
Message.Explanation: The Message Flow properties could not be configured because the Flows parameter were not valid
Message.UserResponse: Check that the classifications specified in the Flows are unique and try again

Message.MsgText: MESSAGE_INDOUBT_WARNING_CWSIP0362=CWSIP0362W: The message with id {0} can not be deleted from destination {1} as the message has been delivered to a consumer.
Message.Explanation: The message cannot be deleted as it has been delivered to a consumer.
Message.UserResponse: Stop any MDB or applications consuming from the destination and try the delete again. If the message still cannot be deleted, review the information center section "Resolving in-doubt transactions" to commit or rollback the transaction.

Message.MsgText: MESSAGE_INDOUBT_WARNING_CWSIP0361=CWSIP0361W: The message with id {0} can not be deleted as the transaction used to add it to destination {1} has not been committed.
Message.Explanation: A message has been sent to the specified destination using a MessageProducer using a transaction. This transaction has not been committed to the destination so the message cannot be deleted.
Message.UserResponse: Review the information center section "Resolving in-doubt transactions" to commit or rollback the transaction.

Message.MsgText: EXCEPTION_DESTINATION_ERROR_CWSIP0295=CWSIP0295E: An attempt to generate an exception report failed so the original message was not sent to exception destination {0} on messaging engine {1}
Message.Explanation: An attempt to route a message to exception destination failed because an exception report was requested but could not be sent for the message.
Message.UserResponse: If the problem persists, additional information might be available if you search for the message ID on the following Web sites: WebSphere Application Server Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/was/support/ WebSphere Application Server for z/OS Support page: http://www.ibm.com/software/webservers/appserv/zos_os390/support/ .

Message.MsgText: USER_NOT_AUTH_INQUIRE_ERROR_CWSIP0314=CWSIP0314E: Inquire access for destination {0} was denied for user with subject {1}
Message.Explanation: A user is not authorized to inquire about the configuration for the destination
Message.UserResponse: If the user should have access to inquire about the configuration of a destination, edit the Inquire access control in the adminstration console by adding the specified user

Message.MsgText: USER_NOT_AUTH_INVOKE_ERROR_CWSIP0316=CWSIP0316E: User {0} must be SIBServerSubject to use invokeCommand() method
Message.Explanation: The user is not authorized to call the invokeCommand() method in the connection
Message.UserResponse: Invoke the method on a connection with SIBServerSubject access

Message.MsgText: MEDIATION_MSG_NOT_RECEIVED_CWSIP0816=CWSIP0816W: A message could not be received from the mediation point associated with destination {0} assigned to WebSphere MQ Server bus member {1}. The WebSphere MQ completion code was {2}. The WebSphere MQ reason code was {3}.
Message.Explanation: A message could not be received from the mediation point associated with the specified destination, assigned to the specified WebSphere MQ Server bus member. The WebSphere MQ completion and reason codes specified can be used to determine why the message could not be received.
Message.UserResponse: Consult the WebSphere MQ documentation to determine the meaning of the completion and reason codes. Perform the appropriate corrective action.

Message.MsgText: REPEATED_MESSAGE_THRESHOLD_REACHED_ON_DESTINATION_CWSIP0795=CWSIP0795W: {0} percent of the messages received by messaging engine {2} for destination {3} transmitted from messaging engine {1} have repeatedly been transmitted to the messaging engine.
Message.Explanation: A high percentage of messages sent from the remote messaging engine have previously been received by this messaging engine, messages will not be duplicated but the performance of the messaging system may be reduce. This message can occur when a sudden burst of messages is transmitted to a messaging engine. Repeated occurrences of this message may indicate the maximum message throughput is being exceeded on a sustained basis.
Message.UserResponse: Investigate whether the rate of production of messages to this messaging engine is too high.
